    "title": "SECURITY FOR COSTS",
    "description": "1. This application is brought by the defendant against plaintiff ,it acts as a remedy to the defendant before trial.\n2. if the plaintiff fails to deposit security for costs ,the suit abets and it can be dismissed under order 26 rule 2 (1) of CPR \n3. if the suit is dismissed , the plaintiff can set aside the order with sufficent cause under order 26 rule 2 (2) CPR\n4.  under order 26 rule 3 of civil procedure rules SI 71-1",
